# Deployment Mode

LotusGift v2 deploys as **one Node process** (`apps/api-gateway`) hosting every business module as a Nest library under `services/*`. Single MongoDB Atlas cluster with collection-namespacing per service (`<service>.<entity>` — e.g. `order.orders`, `inventory.stock_ledger`). Outbox is transport-agnostic via the `OutboxPort` interface — in-process `EventEmitter` for MVP, swap to Upstash Workflow + QStash post-revenue per [docs/runbooks/scaling-up.md](../../docs/runbooks/scaling-up.md).

## Do

- Create new business modules with `nest g library <name>` in `services/`.
- Mount the library inside `apps/api-gateway/src/app.module.ts`.
- Namespace collections: `inventory.stock_ledger`, never bare `stock_ledger`.
- Publish events via `OutboxPort.publish(event, { transactionId })`.

## Don't

- Spin up a separate Nest app per service before the GMV trigger in `scaling-up.md` is hit.
- Provision a separate Mongo cluster per service — Atlas M0 quota = 1 cluster per project.
- Import `EventEmitter2` directly in service code.

## Concrete example

```ts
// services/order-service/src/order.module.ts
@Module({ imports: [DatabaseModule.forFeature('order')], providers: [OrderService] })
export class OrderModule {}

// apps/api-gateway/src/app.module.ts
@Module({ imports: [OrderModule, InventoryModule, RfqModule, /* ... */] })
export class AppModule {}
```

